At least 32 people have been killed in recent flash floods in Iran, a senior Iranian rescue and relief official said on Friday. Mehdi Vallipour, head of the Relief and Rescue Organization of the Iranian Red Crescent Society, also told the official news agency IRNA that 25 people were missing.The heavy rainfalls are expected to continue until Monday and have so far led to flooding in 20 Iranian provinces, causing damage to 100 counties and 300 villages.